he ground shifting under our feet in the present and allows us to speculate on what might happen in the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aBoundariesxHistory. 0aBoundary disputesxHistory. 0aGeopoliticsxHistoryy20th century. 0aGeopoliticsxHistoryy21st century. 4aWestphalian order. 4aempires. 4aglobalization. 4ahistory. 4amigrations. 4anation-state. 4aprotectionism. 4asovereignty. 4awalls. 4awar. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Geopolitics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360663040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503606630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503606630.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles